# Policy4FONDRL2BNN

> **FOND policy via Deep RL → Binary Neural Network → PRP-equivalent DAG**

This project demonstrates an end-to-end pipeline:

```
PDDL domain (blocks_clear) ──► BlocksClearEnv (Gymnasium)
                                       │
                          ┌────────────┴────────────┐
                          ▼                         ▼
              PyG relational encoder       DQN (small MLP)
            (state -> 4-bit features)     (4 -> 32 -> 32 -> 11)
                          │                         │
                          ▼                         ▼
        4-bit feature vector [BlocksCleared, H, VGoal, VStart]
                          │                         │
                          ▼                         ▼
                     Abstract MDP          Q-table (16 × n_actions)
                  (value iteration)               │
                          │                       │
                          └────────► Q-table (16 × 4)  ◄──────┘
                                          │
                                  supervise (CE loss)
                                          │
                                          ▼
                       Brevitas BinaryPolicyNet (BNN)
                                          │
                                          ▼
                                ┌──────────────────────┐
                                │ 16/16 equivalence?   │
                                │ (argmax_Q == argmax_BNN) │
                                └──────────────────────┘
                                          │
                                          ▼
                            PRP policy.out / human_policy.out
                                (equivalent DAG)
```

---

## 1. What this project proves

- **Q-table → PRP policy**: Value-iteration on the 16-state × 4-action MDP yields the
  optimal Q-table. The argmax over actions mirrors the canonical FOND policy by
  Tagawa / Pozanco et al. ([`solutionsByPRP/fond_blocks_clear_human_policy.out`](../PRP_planner-for-relevant-policies/solutionsByPRP/fond_blocks_clear_human_policy.out)).

- **Q-table → BNN → PRP policy**: A Brevitas quantised MLP, supervised by the
  Q-table, achieves **16/16** argmax equivalence across the full 16-state space,
  proving that the binary-weight BNN is a *behaviourally equivalent* representation
  of the Q-table. Re-exporting the BNN's argmax gives an identical PRP policy.

